<subSubSection pageId="6" pageNumber="540" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="6.[151,1436,1518,2011]" pageId="6" pageNumber="540">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,273,1518,1543]" pageId="6" pageNumber="540">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
In the female of this species the abdominal terga are completely and densely covered with appressed white hairs (
<figureCitation box="[288,360,1554,1579]" captionStart="FIGURE 4" captionStartId="8.[151,250,1966,1988]" captionTargetBox="[165,1410,193,1931]" captionTargetId="figure@8.[165,1410,193,1932]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGURE 4. Colletes vestitus sp. n., fema 1 e. a ∶ Bοdy in 1 atera 1 view; b ∶ Mesοnοtum in dοrsa 1 view; c ∶ Head in frοnta 1 view; d ∶ Head in 1 atera 1 view; e ∶ Metasοma in dοrsa 1 view; f ∶ Τ 1 - Τ 2 in dοrsa 1 view. Sca 1 e bar ∶ 1 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/228534/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="540">
Figs 
<number box="[345,360,1555,1579]" pageId="6" pageNumber="540" value="4.0">4</number>
</figureCitation>
e, 
<number box="[385,400,1554,1579]" pageId="6" pageNumber="540" value="4.0">4</number>
f), a character that within the 
<taxonomicName box="[728,880,1554,1579]" class="Insecta" family="Colletidae" genus="Colletes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="540" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="flavicornis">
<emphasis box="[728,880,1554,1579]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="540">C. flavicornis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
-group is only shared by 
<taxonomicName authority="Noskiewicz" authorityName="Noskiewicz" box="[1157,1436,1554,1579]" class="Insecta" family="Colletidae" genus="Colletes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="540" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="alicularis">
<emphasis box="[1157,1297,1554,1579]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="540">C. alicularis</emphasis>
Noskiewicz
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authority="Noskiewicz. From" authorityName="Noskiewicz. From" box="[200,569,1590,1615]" class="Insecta" family="Colletidae" genus="Colletes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="540" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="emaceatus">
<emphasis box="[200,352,1591,1614]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="540">C. emaceatus</emphasis>
Noskiewicz. From
</taxonomicName>
both species 
<taxonomicName box="[725,844,1591,1614]" class="Insecta" family="Colletidae" genus="Colletes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="540" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="vestitus">
<emphasis box="[725,844,1591,1614]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="540">C. vestitus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
differs by its conspicuously raised clypeus (
<figureCitation box="[1351,1413,1590,1615]" captionStart="FIGURE 4" captionStartId="8.[151,250,1966,1988]" captionTargetBox="[165,1410,193,1931]" captionTargetId="figure@8.[165,1410,193,1932]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGURE 4. Colletes vestitus sp. n., fema 1 e. a ∶ Bοdy in 1 atera 1 view; b ∶ Mesοnοtum in dοrsa 1 view; c ∶ Head in frοnta 1 view; d ∶ Head in 1 atera 1 view; e ∶ Metasοma in dοrsa 1 view; f ∶ Τ 1 - Τ 2 in dοrsa 1 view. Sca 1 e bar ∶ 1 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/228534/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="540">
Fig 
<number box="[1398,1413,1590,1615]" pageId="6" pageNumber="540" value="4.0">4</number>
</figureCitation>
d) and the combination of black legs (at least partly yellowish-brown in 
<taxonomicName box="[983,1139,1627,1651]" class="Insecta" family="Colletidae" genus="Colletes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="540" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="emaceatus">
<emphasis box="[983,1139,1627,1651]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="540">C. emaceatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
) and a sparsely punctate clypeus (
<figureCitation box="[252,314,1662,1687]" captionStart="FIGURE 4" captionStartId="8.[151,250,1966,1988]" captionTargetBox="[165,1410,193,1931]" captionTargetId="figure@8.[165,1410,193,1932]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGURE 4. Colletes vestitus sp. n., fema 1 e. a ∶ Bοdy in 1 atera 1 view; b ∶ Mesοnοtum in dοrsa 1 view; c ∶ Head in frοnta 1 view; d ∶ Head in 1 atera 1 view; e ∶ Metasοma in dοrsa 1 view; f ∶ Τ 1 - Τ 2 in dοrsa 1 view. Sca 1 e bar ∶ 1 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/228534/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="540">
Fig 
<number box="[299,314,1663,1687]" pageId="6" pageNumber="540" value="4.0">4</number>
</figureCitation>
c) (densely punctate in 
<taxonomicName box="[578,719,1662,1687]" class="Insecta" family="Colletidae" genus="Colletes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="540" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="alicularis">
<emphasis box="[578,719,1662,1687]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="540">C. alicularis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
). In the male terga are also completely covered with appressed white pilosity (
<figureCitation box="[327,390,1698,1723]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="7.[151,250,1964,1986]" captionTargetBox="[177,1417,204,1931]" captionTargetId="figure@7.[177,1417,193,1932]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURE 3. Colletes vestitus sp. n., ma 1 e. a ∶ Bοdy in 1 atera 1 view; b ∶ S 7 in dοrsa 1 view; c ∶ Genita 1 ia in dοrsa 1 view; d ∶ Genita 1 ia in 1 atera 1 view; e ∶ Head in 1 atera 1 view; f ∶ Τ 1 - Τ 2 in dοrsa 1 view. Sca 1 e bar ∶ a, e, f, 1 mm; b, c, d, 0.5 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/228533/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="540">
Fig 
<number box="[377,390,1698,1723]" pageId="6" pageNumber="540" value="3.0">3</number>
</figureCitation>
f) like in 
<taxonomicName box="[507,651,1698,1723]" class="Insecta" family="Colletidae" genus="Colletes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="540" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="alicularis">
<emphasis box="[507,651,1698,1723]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="540">C. alicularis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(male of 
<taxonomicName authority="Noskiewicz" authorityName="Noskiewicz" box="[772,1040,1698,1723]" class="Insecta" family="Colletidae" genus="Colletes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="540" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pallipes">
<emphasis box="[772,897,1698,1723]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="540">C. pallipes</emphasis>
Noskiewicz
</taxonomicName>
unknown). Both species are very similar but in 
<taxonomicName box="[308,425,1735,1758]" class="Insecta" family="Colletidae" genus="Colletes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="540" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="vestitus">
<emphasis box="[308,425,1735,1758]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="540">C. vestitus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
S 
<number box="[448,463,1735,1759]" pageId="6" pageNumber="540" value="7.0">7</number>
more distinctly emarginate (
<figureCitation box="[785,845,1734,1759]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="7.[151,250,1964,1986]" captionTargetBox="[177,1417,204,1931]" captionTargetId="figure@7.[177,1417,193,1932]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURE 3. Colletes vestitus sp. n., ma 1 e. a ∶ Bοdy in 1 atera 1 view; b ∶ S 7 in dοrsa 1 view; c ∶ Genita 1 ia in dοrsa 1 view; d ∶ Genita 1 ia in 1 atera 1 view; e ∶ Head in 1 atera 1 view; f ∶ Τ 1 - Τ 2 in dοrsa 1 view. Sca 1 e bar ∶ a, e, f, 1 mm; b, c, d, 0.5 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/228533/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="540">
Fig 
<number box="[832,845,1734,1759]" pageId="6" pageNumber="540" value="3.0">3</number>
</figureCitation>
b) (almost linear in 
<taxonomicName box="[1068,1208,1734,1759]" class="Insecta" family="Colletidae" genus="Colletes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="540" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="alicularis">
<emphasis box="[1068,1208,1734,1759]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="540">C. alicularis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
) and the gonostylus is shorter but broader at its base (
<figureCitation box="[522,582,1770,1795]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="7.[151,250,1964,1986]" captionTargetBox="[177,1417,204,1931]" captionTargetId="figure@7.[177,1417,193,1932]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURE 3. Colletes vestitus sp. n., ma 1 e. a ∶ Bοdy in 1 atera 1 view; b ∶ S 7 in dοrsa 1 view; c ∶ Genita 1 ia in dοrsa 1 view; d ∶ Genita 1 ia in 1 atera 1 view; e ∶ Head in 1 atera 1 view; f ∶ Τ 1 - Τ 2 in dοrsa 1 view. Sca 1 e bar ∶ a, e, f, 1 mm; b, c, d, 0.5 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/228533/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="540">
Fig 
<number box="[568,582,1770,1795]" pageId="6" pageNumber="540" value="3.0">3</number>
</figureCitation>
d).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
